1
00:00:37,267 --> 00:00:38,967
<i> I admit, Dear...</i>

2
00:00:39,100 --> 00:00:41,567
<i>that I was so wrong
to ruin your party.</i>

3
00:00:41,700 --> 00:00:43,167
<i>- You're awake now!
- Mommy!</i>

4
00:00:43,300 --> 00:00:45,500
<i>- Dear, you're awake....
- Mommy, leave me alone!</i>

5
00:00:45,633 --> 00:00:47,467
<i>- Hazel?
- Auntie Felma!</i>

6
00:00:47,600 --> 00:00:48,767
<i> How did you get in here?</i>

7
00:00:50,567 --> 00:00:52,933
<i>Madam Hazel, you're being
charged with physical assault</i>

8
00:00:53,067 --> 00:00:57,067
<i>resulting in serious physical
injuries.</i>

9
00:00:57,200 --> 00:00:58,233
<i> How's the interview?</i>

10
00:00:58,367 --> 00:00:59,833
<i>I wasn't hired.
There's nothing wrong</i>

11
00:00:59,967 --> 00:01:02,333
<i>with those jobs,
they are decent.</i>

12
00:01:02,467 --> 00:01:03,533
<i> But I don't like them.</i>

13
00:01:03,667 --> 00:01:05,167
<i> If you want an easy job,</i>

14
00:01:05,300 --> 00:01:06,767
<i>then you should
just return to FMP.</i>

15
00:01:06,900 --> 00:01:08,667
<i>You got hired as a virtual
assistant?</i>

16
00:01:08,833 --> 00:01:10,733
<i>- Congrats!
- Thank you.</i>

17
00:01:10,867 --> 00:01:12,700
<i>- What are you doing here?
- Hey, classmate!</i>

18
00:01:12,833 --> 00:01:14,733
<i>I thought you didn't need
my help anymore?</i>

19
00:01:14,867 --> 00:01:17,933
<i>I was banned from San Rafael
Doctors Hospital.</i>

20
00:01:18,067 --> 00:01:19,300
<i> Help me get in.</i>

21
00:01:19,433 --> 00:01:20,700
<i> Please take off your masks.</i>

22
00:01:20,833 --> 00:01:21,967
<i> My wife is pregnant.</i>

23
00:01:22,100 --> 00:01:23,200
<i> Here, this will wake you up.</i>

24
00:01:23,333 --> 00:01:25,400
<i>Jessica's room
is on the 4th floor.</i>

25
00:01:25,533 --> 00:01:27,233
<i> Room 411.</i>

26
00:01:30,500 --> 00:01:32,867
Manuel, I'll go home for now.

27
00:01:33,000 --> 00:01:34,467
I'll take care of Coleen first.

28
00:01:34,600 --> 00:01:36,900
She might get upset again
if I don't.

29
00:01:37,033 --> 00:01:38,233
Yes.

30
00:01:38,367 --> 00:01:41,367
She might think you've forgotten
about her again.

31
00:01:42,300 --> 00:01:43,967
I'm glad you're laughing now.

32
00:01:46,200 --> 00:01:47,267
It's because of you, Felma.

33
00:01:50,267 --> 00:01:51,500
Thank you.

34
00:01:56,367 --> 00:01:58,567
I'll walk you to the elevator.

35
00:02:01,433 --> 00:02:02,500
Let me have my bag.

36
00:02:50,267 --> 00:02:52,567
I asked Attorney Yeban
to come here.

37
00:02:52,700 --> 00:02:53,767
So he could talk to you.

38
00:02:54,733 --> 00:02:55,700
He's on his way up here.

39
00:03:03,867 --> 00:03:05,433
Why?

40
00:03:05,567 --> 00:03:07,633
I want to thank you
for staying with me.

41
00:03:08,733 --> 00:03:10,033
And for not leaving me,

42
00:03:10,167 --> 00:03:14,400
not until Jessica woke up.

43
00:03:17,900 --> 00:03:19,667
Thank you, Felma.

44
00:03:22,067 --> 00:03:23,700
You know...

45
00:03:25,300 --> 00:03:27,367
I honestly don't know
how I'm going to face all this

46
00:03:27,500 --> 00:03:29,267
without you.

47
00:03:29,933 --> 00:03:32,100
Felma, please let me know
if you need anything.

48
00:03:32,233 --> 00:03:34,667
I'll do everything for you.

49
00:03:34,800 --> 00:03:36,367
For our children.

50
00:03:43,400 --> 00:03:45,733
<i> You're monsters.</i>

51
00:03:45,867 --> 00:03:47,133
<i> Especially you, Felma.</i>

52
00:03:48,533 --> 00:03:50,300
<i>- Felma!
- Jessica!</i>

53
00:03:53,900 --> 00:03:55,333
<i> Jessica!</i>

54
00:03:55,467 --> 00:03:57,967
<i> Jessica! Jessica!</i>

55
00:03:58,100 --> 00:03:59,600
<i>Ma'am, you have to come with us.</i>

56
00:03:59,733 --> 00:04:01,633
<i>No! Let go of me!
My daughter is in the hospital!</i>

57
00:04:01,767 --> 00:04:03,467
<i> You're a monster, Hazel!</i>

58
00:04:03,600 --> 00:04:04,967
<i>If anything happens to Jessica,</i>

59
00:04:05,100 --> 00:04:07,600
<i>I won't just file
for physical assault!</i>

60
00:04:07,733 --> 00:04:09,167
<i>I'll charge you
with murder or homicide!</i>

61
00:04:09,300 --> 00:04:10,433
<i> No!</i>

62
00:04:10,567 --> 00:04:12,233
<i>- Dad!
- I won't hurt you.</i>

63
00:04:12,367 --> 00:04:15,100
<i> Mom, don't go near me, please!</i>

64
00:04:15,233 --> 00:04:16,867
<i> Dad! Dad!</i>

65
00:04:17,000 --> 00:04:19,500
<i> She's my daughter!</i>

66
00:04:19,633 --> 00:04:21,133
<i>And as for your husband,
he's charging you</i>

67
00:04:21,267 --> 00:04:26,667
<i>with physical assault resulting
in serious physical injuries.</i>

68
00:04:26,800 --> 00:04:29,400
<i> That's up to 6 years in jail.</i>

69
00:04:32,933 --> 00:04:35,967
<i>Don't blame me for what you did
to your daughter.</i>

70
00:04:36,100 --> 00:04:37,200
<i> Just leave!</i>

71
00:04:37,333 --> 00:04:39,133
<i> You both have no shame.</i>

72
00:04:39,267 --> 00:04:40,700
<i>You really had to flirt here,
of all places?</i>

73
00:04:40,833 --> 00:04:43,333
<i>- Let go of me!
- No, Hazel!</i>

74
00:04:43,467 --> 00:04:44,733
<i> Did you hear your daughter?</i>

75
00:04:44,867 --> 00:04:46,300
<i> Don't you feel bad for her?</i>

76
00:04:46,433 --> 00:04:47,567
<i> She's scared of you!</i>

77
00:04:47,700 --> 00:04:50,100
<i>Who do you think you are to act
like a mother to my child?</i>

78
00:04:50,233 --> 00:04:52,800
<i>Who do you think you are?
Jessica is my daughter!</i>

79
00:04:52,933 --> 00:04:54,567
<i> Fine, Felma.</i>

80
00:04:54,700 --> 00:04:56,833
<i>I once stole Manuel
from you, too.</i>

81
00:04:56,967 --> 00:04:58,200
<i> So, go ahead.</i>

82
00:04:58,333 --> 00:05:00,267
<i>I can endure it,
even if you steal him from me.</i>

83
00:05:00,400 --> 00:05:03,100
<i> But my daughter? Never.</i>

84
00:05:03,267 --> 00:05:04,967
<i> So don't ever touch her.</i>

85
00:05:08,433 --> 00:05:10,167
<i>Before you can take her away
from me,</i>

86
00:05:10,300 --> 00:05:12,433
<i> you have to kill me first.</i>

87
00:05:12,567 --> 00:05:13,800
<i> I won't let go of her.</i>

88
00:05:16,667 --> 00:05:18,233
Please hug Coleen for me.

89
00:05:18,367 --> 00:05:19,500
I will.

90
00:05:20,933 --> 00:05:22,267
- Attorney.
- Hi.

91
00:05:22,400 --> 00:05:24,900
I'm so sorry, I got stuck
with several clients sa firm.

92
00:05:25,033 --> 00:05:25,933
It's okay.

93
00:05:26,067 --> 00:05:30,467
So, are you ready
to talk about the case

94
00:05:30,600 --> 00:05:32,200
we're going to file
against your wife?

95
00:05:32,333 --> 00:05:33,367
Yes, Attorney.

96
00:05:37,367 --> 00:05:38,433
- Hazel?
- Hazel?

97
00:05:41,933 --> 00:05:43,900
Won't you really stop
making trouble?

98
00:05:48,833 --> 00:05:49,933
Manuel.

99
00:05:50,867 --> 00:05:52,033
Manuel.

100
00:05:53,633 --> 00:05:55,167
I'm begging you.

101
00:05:56,033 --> 00:05:57,700
I want to see Jessica.

102
00:05:58,533 --> 00:05:59,767
Even for just a while.

103
00:06:00,500 --> 00:06:02,033
Even if it's only for a second.

104
00:06:12,867 --> 00:06:15,333
I only want to ask
for our daughter's forgiveness.

105
00:06:16,300 --> 00:06:17,633
Please, Manuel.

106
00:06:18,700 --> 00:06:20,967
Don't deny me that chance.

107
00:06:21,100 --> 00:06:22,200
Manuel, I'm begging you.

108
00:06:22,700 --> 00:06:24,467
Hazel, could you please get up!

109
00:06:24,867 --> 00:06:27,600
Leave, before I get the guards
to drag you out!

110
00:06:30,700 --> 00:06:33,000
Felma, Felma.

111
00:06:35,400 --> 00:06:36,733
Felma...

112
00:06:36,867 --> 00:06:37,933
you're a mother, too.

113
00:06:39,767 --> 00:06:42,533
I know you understand
what I feel.

114
00:06:43,667 --> 00:06:45,633
Please help me with Jessica.

115
00:06:46,733 --> 00:06:47,900
I'm begging you.

116
00:06:49,200 --> 00:06:50,067
Felma.

117
00:06:50,200 --> 00:06:51,933
Felma, don't listen to her.

118
00:06:58,067 --> 00:07:03,967
Manuel, perhaps you should talk
to Jessica first.

119
00:07:21,833 --> 00:07:23,300
Coleen...

120
00:07:23,433 --> 00:07:26,467
your<i> adobo</i> in tomatoes
looks so delicious.

121
00:07:27,500 --> 00:07:29,233
Didang, where is my mom?

122
00:07:29,367 --> 00:07:32,900
Mom's not answering
my calls or texts.

123
00:07:33,600 --> 00:07:35,600
I even cooked for her.

124
00:07:36,733 --> 00:07:39,900
Maybe she's going to stay
the night at the hospital.

125
00:07:40,033 --> 00:07:42,267
Maybe Jessica still needs her.

126
00:07:43,467 --> 00:07:44,900
Come on.

127
00:07:52,433 --> 00:07:54,700
I just wish she'd at least send
an update.

128
00:07:55,967 --> 00:07:59,100
She has a daughter
waiting for her.

129
00:07:59,233 --> 00:08:00,767
I see...

130
00:08:00,900 --> 00:08:02,400
hold on.

131
00:08:02,700 --> 00:08:07,267
Coleen, what's making you
so jealous of Jessica?

132
00:08:07,533 --> 00:08:08,733
Hey.

133
00:08:08,867 --> 00:08:12,867
Didang, I won't get jealous
of Jessica ever.

134
00:08:13,000 --> 00:08:14,100
What are you saying?

135
00:08:15,433 --> 00:08:16,400
Wow.

136
00:08:16,533 --> 00:08:17,767
- No, it doesn't seem so.
- But....

137
00:08:19,133 --> 00:08:21,233
Really, really.

138
00:08:22,867 --> 00:08:24,167
It smells of jealousy.

139
00:08:24,300 --> 00:08:25,500
Didang...

140
00:08:27,567 --> 00:08:29,633
I'm just a little hurt by mom.

141
00:08:31,300 --> 00:08:34,100
It feels like
she's forgetting me.

142
00:08:34,233 --> 00:08:35,067
So, you really are jealous.

143
00:08:35,200 --> 00:08:36,733
I can see it.

144
00:08:37,900 --> 00:08:39,233
It shows jealousy.

145
00:08:39,367 --> 00:08:42,067
Besides the smell,
it also looks like jealousy.

146
00:08:42,200 --> 00:08:43,367
Stop it.

147
00:08:44,967 --> 00:08:47,367
I know we've been hurting each
other again and again.

148
00:08:49,133 --> 00:08:52,000
Can we just set that aside?

149
00:08:52,133 --> 00:08:53,467
For Jessica.

150
00:08:54,400 --> 00:08:55,967
Let's not fight for now.

151
00:08:57,567 --> 00:08:59,200
Help me with her, please.

152
00:08:59,333 --> 00:09:00,433
I want to see her.

153
00:09:00,567 --> 00:09:01,733
I want to talk to her.

154
00:09:03,000 --> 00:09:05,200
The nerve of you, Hazel!

155
00:09:06,067 --> 00:09:07,233
You badmouth Felma,

156
00:09:07,367 --> 00:09:09,133
and now you're begging her?

157
00:09:10,367 --> 00:09:12,533
Manuel, I'm desperate.

158
00:09:14,033 --> 00:09:15,833
I want to see Jessica.

159
00:09:15,967 --> 00:09:17,467
I want to see her.

160
00:09:17,600 --> 00:09:19,133
I want to talk to her.

161
00:09:19,267 --> 00:09:21,600
You're not getting near
my daughter!

162
00:09:26,600 --> 00:09:27,700
Manuel.

163
00:09:29,167 --> 00:09:32,833
Maybe you should ask
Jessica first.

164
00:09:48,533 --> 00:09:49,567
I didn't know you were home,
Jeff.

165
00:09:55,167 --> 00:09:56,333
What's the matter, Jeff?

166
00:09:57,900 --> 00:09:59,633
Daisy, I need money for fare.

167
00:10:00,633 --> 00:10:02,800
Jopet is offering me a job.

168
00:10:02,967 --> 00:10:05,600
But I only have 2000 pesos
left in my bank.

169
00:10:06,633 --> 00:10:08,367
I don't want to use that because
it's the maintaining balance.

170
00:10:08,500 --> 00:10:10,967
If it goes down, the penalty
might be even bigger.

171
00:10:12,733 --> 00:10:15,033
All that's left in my budget
is for the electricity bill.

172
00:10:16,100 --> 00:10:17,633
Even just 500 pesos?

173
00:10:19,500 --> 00:10:20,700
I'll return it as soon as I can.

174
00:10:21,800 --> 00:10:23,800
The due date's next week, right?

175
00:10:32,233 --> 00:10:33,700
Thank you.

176
00:10:38,767 --> 00:10:41,167
Don't you want to go back
to your mom, Jeff?

177
00:10:42,367 --> 00:10:43,933
Or at least to FMP?

178
00:10:45,800 --> 00:10:48,400
Jeff, I'm not complaining,
but...

179
00:10:48,533 --> 00:10:50,367
I know I'm already
a burden to you.

180
00:10:52,000 --> 00:10:54,533
But I hope you don't force me
to return to FMP.

181
00:10:56,667 --> 00:10:58,633
I promise, I'll have work
when I come back later.

182
00:11:06,800 --> 00:11:09,800
Dear, if it were up to me,

183
00:11:09,967 --> 00:11:11,667
I wouldn't let your mom see you.

184
00:11:13,600 --> 00:11:15,100
But...

185
00:11:15,233 --> 00:11:17,033
your Auntie Felma is right.

186
00:11:17,167 --> 00:11:19,600
You have the right to decide.

187
00:11:23,933 --> 00:11:25,500
Dad, I don't know.

188
00:11:27,800 --> 00:11:29,867
Mom hurt me too many times.

189
00:11:31,067 --> 00:11:33,567
I don't think I can trust her
anymore.

190
00:11:35,233 --> 00:11:37,067
Okay, I'll let her know.

191
00:11:37,200 --> 00:11:38,300
Hold on, Manuel.

192
00:11:39,600 --> 00:11:42,567
Oh, Jessica...

193
00:11:42,733 --> 00:11:45,933
can't you really give your mom
a chance anymore?

194
00:11:47,133 --> 00:11:49,400
She only wants to ask
for your forgiveness.

195
00:11:49,533 --> 00:11:50,500
Felma.

196
00:11:50,633 --> 00:11:51,667
Manuel...

197
00:11:53,467 --> 00:11:57,033
We both understand
the pain parents feel

198
00:11:57,167 --> 00:11:59,367
when their children
push them away.

199
00:12:00,533 --> 00:12:01,567
It hurts.

200
00:12:05,600 --> 00:12:06,767
Jessica,

201
00:12:09,500 --> 00:12:11,100
just listen to your mom.

202
00:12:14,233 --> 00:12:15,433
Don't worry.

203
00:12:17,633 --> 00:12:19,733
Your dad will stay with you.

204
00:12:29,767 --> 00:12:30,967
All right.

205
00:12:32,700 --> 00:12:35,167
I'll talk to mom.

206
00:13:05,400 --> 00:13:06,133
Dear.

207
00:13:09,300 --> 00:13:10,300
Jessica.

208
00:13:12,667 --> 00:13:14,200
I'm so sorry, Dear.

209
00:13:16,233 --> 00:13:17,333
I hurt you.

210
00:13:18,733 --> 00:13:20,433
I didn't mean to.

211
00:13:20,567 --> 00:13:21,767
Please forgive me.

212
00:13:29,033 --> 00:13:31,200
Dear, please don't be
scared of me.

213
00:13:34,533 --> 00:13:35,633
Please.

214
00:13:38,200 --> 00:13:40,000
Please give me a chance.

215
00:13:41,000 --> 00:13:42,700
I'll make it up to you.

216
00:13:42,833 --> 00:13:44,033
I promise.

217
00:13:47,400 --> 00:13:48,433
Dear...

218
00:13:49,933 --> 00:13:51,333
I'm still your mom.

219
00:13:53,267 --> 00:13:55,900
I don't want to stop being
your mom.

220
00:13:58,767 --> 00:13:59,767
I know...

221
00:14:00,900 --> 00:14:03,200
I know I've done you
a lot of wrong,

222
00:14:03,333 --> 00:14:04,667
but...

223
00:14:06,033 --> 00:14:07,667
I can fix that.

224
00:14:10,200 --> 00:14:11,233
I promise,

225
00:14:11,367 --> 00:14:12,600
I'll fix it, Dear.

226
00:14:13,700 --> 00:14:15,267
We'll start all over again.

227
00:14:16,800 --> 00:14:18,767
We were happy before, right?

228
00:14:20,600 --> 00:14:22,133
We can bring that back.

229
00:14:24,000 --> 00:14:25,433
But, please, Dear.

230
00:14:27,700 --> 00:14:29,867
Don't push me away.

231
00:14:31,733 --> 00:14:34,800
I can't bear it,
my one and only baby.

232
00:14:38,567 --> 00:14:39,633
Dear...

233
00:14:41,600 --> 00:14:42,833
please forgive me.

234
00:14:49,500 --> 00:14:50,967
I'm begging you, Dear.

235
00:14:51,900 --> 00:14:53,567
Please.

236
00:14:53,700 --> 00:14:54,900
Please forgive me.

237
00:14:57,900 --> 00:15:00,100
I will forgive you, Mommy.

238
00:15:02,100 --> 00:15:04,100
But I have a request.

239
00:15:05,533 --> 00:15:07,100
Of course, Dear, anything.

240
00:15:07,900 --> 00:15:09,633
Tell me what it is.

241
00:15:12,067 --> 00:15:13,600
Mommy.

242
00:15:13,733 --> 00:15:16,567
Mommy, please stop harassing
Auntie Felma.

243
00:15:17,933 --> 00:15:20,100
She's nothing but good to us.

244
00:15:21,133 --> 00:15:23,100
Mommy, she doesn't deserve...

245
00:15:23,233 --> 00:15:25,167
the way you humiliate her.

246
00:15:26,800 --> 00:15:28,200
And please,

247
00:15:31,233 --> 00:15:33,433
let me and daddy be for now.

248
00:15:34,667 --> 00:15:36,267
Mom, we need space.

249
00:15:40,367 --> 00:15:41,967
Sure.

250
00:15:42,400 --> 00:15:43,567
Of course, Dear.

251
00:15:44,133 --> 00:15:45,800
Of course.

252
00:15:45,933 --> 00:15:49,400
But please, forgive me.

253
00:15:51,167 --> 00:15:52,300
Can you do that?

254
00:15:53,133 --> 00:15:54,767
I'll do what you want, Dear.

255
00:15:54,900 --> 00:15:57,700
Anything, I'll do it.

256
00:15:57,833 --> 00:15:59,833
But please forgive me.

257
00:16:17,833 --> 00:16:23,167
Manuel, I also have a request.

258
00:16:25,133 --> 00:16:26,167
Can we just...

259
00:16:27,633 --> 00:16:30,300
settle this without
going to court?

260
00:16:31,600 --> 00:16:33,633
The truth finally comes out.

261
00:16:33,767 --> 00:16:37,000
You're only pleading
for me to drop the case.

262
00:16:37,333 --> 00:16:38,967
You even used my daughter.

263
00:16:50,167 --> 00:16:51,200
It's not like that.

264
00:16:52,733 --> 00:16:54,900
I just don't want this
to end up in court.

265
00:16:56,133 --> 00:16:59,033
But if that's what you want,

266
00:17:00,467 --> 00:17:01,900
there's nothing
I can do about it.

267
00:17:03,467 --> 00:17:06,133
If I end up in jail,

268
00:17:06,267 --> 00:17:07,967
I just don't want Jessica
to lose her mom.

269
00:17:15,433 --> 00:17:17,967
Dad, please,
I don't want any more trouble.

270
00:17:19,000 --> 00:17:21,000
If you pursue the case,

271
00:17:21,133 --> 00:17:24,600
the court will ask me things
about what happened.

272
00:17:24,733 --> 00:17:29,500
Dad, why it happened
and why we are in this mess.

273
00:17:31,400 --> 00:17:36,233
I don't want to tell someone
else about our problems.

274
00:17:36,367 --> 00:17:38,367
And Auntie Felma, Dad.

275
00:17:40,067 --> 00:17:41,200
She'll get involved, too.

276
00:17:41,333 --> 00:17:42,533
I don't want that to happen.

277
00:17:46,967 --> 00:17:48,667
You're such a good kid.

278
00:17:57,500 --> 00:17:59,100
Daisy was right, Bro.

279
00:17:59,933 --> 00:18:01,200
Why don't you go back
to Auntie Felma?

280
00:18:01,333 --> 00:18:03,733
So you can go back
to living the good life.

281
00:18:03,867 --> 00:18:05,500
Seriously, Jopet?

282
00:18:05,633 --> 00:18:07,633
If that's all you have to say,
I'm going home.

283
00:18:07,767 --> 00:18:09,033
Hey, wait.

284
00:18:09,167 --> 00:18:10,667
You're so dramatic.

285
00:18:10,800 --> 00:18:11,900
Come on.

286
00:18:12,033 --> 00:18:13,667
I'm just giving you a real talk.

287
00:18:13,800 --> 00:18:14,867
Chill.

288
00:18:15,000 --> 00:18:17,500
The job you are talking about,
what's the update?

289
00:18:19,033 --> 00:18:20,700
Here it is, here it is.

290
00:18:20,833 --> 00:18:22,067
I'm calling now.

291
00:18:22,233 --> 00:18:23,700
You're being impatient,
are you in a rush?

292
00:18:23,833 --> 00:18:25,567
- Go on, call him.
- Okay, I'm on it.

293
00:18:27,700 --> 00:18:29,367
<i> Oh, Jopet.</i>

294
00:18:29,500 --> 00:18:32,267
Boss, I'm here with my friend.

295
00:18:32,400 --> 00:18:34,100
The one I was hoping
to recommend to Shop Point.

296
00:18:34,233 --> 00:18:36,333
He rides the motorcycle, right?

297
00:18:36,467 --> 00:18:37,933
Yes, Sir, this is Jeffrey.

298
00:18:38,067 --> 00:18:40,267
Yes, I know how to ride
a motorcycle.

299
00:18:40,400 --> 00:18:42,300
<i> Okay, you're hired.</i>

300
00:18:43,333 --> 00:18:44,600
Really, Sir?

301
00:18:44,733 --> 00:18:46,733
Thank you, Sir!
Thank you!

302
00:18:46,867 --> 00:18:48,067
Thank you, Sir, bye.

303
00:18:48,733 --> 00:18:50,233
- Is that real?
- Yes.

304
00:18:50,367 --> 00:18:51,400
- Nice!
- Congrats.

305
00:18:51,533 --> 00:18:52,600
That was fast.

306
00:18:52,733 --> 00:18:54,067
Go ahead, do this.

307
00:18:54,200 --> 00:18:55,500
No, I'm good.

308
00:18:56,633 --> 00:18:58,667
What needs to be done?

309
00:18:58,800 --> 00:19:00,233
- You just have to screw it.
- Just that?

310
00:19:00,367 --> 00:19:01,767
Can't you do it?

311
00:19:01,900 --> 00:19:03,567
When will I start?

312
00:19:04,267 --> 00:19:05,633
We'll ask him again.
But you're all good.

313
00:19:05,767 --> 00:19:07,333
- Okay.
- Congrats.

314
00:19:09,367 --> 00:19:10,900
Look at it, Joel.

315
00:19:11,033 --> 00:19:12,200
It's legit, right?

316
00:19:12,333 --> 00:19:15,533
They have security and trade
authority registration.

317
00:19:15,667 --> 00:19:17,467
Oh, there's a bank statements.

318
00:19:18,567 --> 00:19:19,767
It's legit, right?

319
00:19:20,967 --> 00:19:22,967
I've seen a lot like that,

320
00:19:23,100 --> 00:19:24,667
and they ended up as scams.

321
00:19:24,800 --> 00:19:26,200
Not this time.

322
00:19:26,333 --> 00:19:28,200
Elvie is a decent person.

323
00:19:28,367 --> 00:19:30,300
And she's been wealthy
for a long time.

324
00:19:30,433 --> 00:19:33,833
This business made her
even richer.

325
00:19:35,900 --> 00:19:38,133
So? Aren't you still going
to invest?

326
00:19:39,333 --> 00:19:40,800
I've already invested in it.

327
00:19:41,733 --> 00:19:42,533
What?

328
00:19:44,000 --> 00:19:44,967
Why are you in a rush?

329
00:19:47,200 --> 00:19:48,667
You know why.

330
00:19:48,800 --> 00:19:50,733
I've already told you.

331
00:19:50,867 --> 00:19:55,000
Oh, yes, you want to prove
yourself to your mom.

332
00:19:56,533 --> 00:20:00,833
Andrea, I just don't want
your success

333
00:20:00,967 --> 00:20:03,033
to be driven by your anger
at your mother.

334
00:20:04,467 --> 00:20:08,000
I thought you didn't want
to meddle in my life?

335
00:20:10,767 --> 00:20:11,800
I'm sorry.

336
00:20:13,567 --> 00:20:15,967
I feel sad for what's happening
between you and your mom.

337
00:20:19,200 --> 00:20:20,633
Come on, Joel.

338
00:20:20,767 --> 00:20:22,733
Can we not bring mom
into this conversation?

339
00:20:22,867 --> 00:20:24,633
Please.

340
00:20:24,767 --> 00:20:26,333
I don't want to talk about her.

341
00:20:26,467 --> 00:20:27,367
Okay.

342
00:20:27,500 --> 00:20:28,700
Sorry.

343
00:20:35,700 --> 00:20:37,600
Nurse, what happened to mom?

344
00:20:37,733 --> 00:20:40,267
Please calm down, Ma'am,
calm down.

345
00:20:40,400 --> 00:20:41,333
Please tend to her.

346
00:20:41,467 --> 00:20:42,700
Her BP is dropping.

347
00:20:42,833 --> 00:20:44,900
Please help us.

348
00:20:45,033 --> 00:20:46,000
Mom.

349
00:20:48,800 --> 00:20:50,533
Respiratory distress

350
00:20:50,667 --> 00:20:52,400
- O2 mask, please.
- Okay.

351
00:20:52,533 --> 00:20:54,200
Ma'am, what's going on
with my mom?

352
00:21:10,700 --> 00:21:11,700
Try to relax, Ma'am.

353
00:21:14,333 --> 00:21:15,900
Try to relax, okay?

354
00:21:17,867 --> 00:21:19,600
Don't worry.

355
00:21:19,733 --> 00:21:20,767
She'll be fine.

356
00:21:28,667 --> 00:21:30,167
Next time don't panic.

357
00:21:30,300 --> 00:21:31,533
- Okay?
- Yes, Ma'am.

358
00:21:31,667 --> 00:21:34,533
And breathe before you talk
to the patient.

359
00:21:34,667 --> 00:21:35,633
Okay.

360
00:21:35,767 --> 00:21:37,467
Inform Dr. Zorbano, okay?

361
00:21:37,600 --> 00:21:39,433
Update him on the patient's
status.

362
00:21:39,567 --> 00:21:41,167
- Yes, I will.
- Okay.

363
00:21:45,567 --> 00:21:47,633
Everybody's raving about you.

364
00:21:47,767 --> 00:21:50,000
People say you're amazing.

365
00:21:50,133 --> 00:21:53,967
Wow, trying to impress already
on the first day?

366
00:21:54,100 --> 00:21:55,533
What a show-off.

367
00:21:56,500 --> 00:21:57,833
Why?

368
00:21:57,967 --> 00:21:59,433
Are you threatened?

369
00:21:59,567 --> 00:22:00,500
Hell no!

370
00:22:00,633 --> 00:22:02,833
Before you leave,
swing by my office.

371
00:22:02,967 --> 00:22:04,033
We'll have coffee.

372
00:22:04,167 --> 00:22:07,533
I've gotta come up
with a harder task for you,

373
00:22:07,667 --> 00:22:10,333
just to see you sweat.

374
00:22:10,467 --> 00:22:11,867
- Sure.
- See you.

375
00:22:12,000 --> 00:22:13,667
There's still something I need
to finish, wait.

376
00:22:16,833 --> 00:22:19,633
<i>Mommy, no!
Don't come near me!</i>

377
00:22:19,767 --> 00:22:21,100
<i> Mommy!</i>

378
00:22:21,233 --> 00:22:23,700
<i> No! No!</i>

379
00:22:23,833 --> 00:22:25,567
<i> No, I'm not going to hurt you!</i>

380
00:22:25,700 --> 00:22:27,333
<i> Dear, don't be scared of me.</i>

381
00:22:36,467 --> 00:22:38,467
You're on another level, Sis!

382
00:22:38,600 --> 00:22:41,167
Martyrdom unlocked.

383
00:22:41,300 --> 00:22:43,200
Level 100 right away!

384
00:22:43,333 --> 00:22:45,167
You're really the one
who mediated

385
00:22:45,300 --> 00:22:46,433
between Hazel and Jessica?

386
00:22:46,567 --> 00:22:48,700
She's your enemy
but you helped her.

387
00:22:48,867 --> 00:22:50,567
You're really something.

388
00:22:50,933 --> 00:22:52,900
Sometimes, you make me want to
smack you!

389
00:22:53,433 --> 00:22:58,000
I saw my situation with Jeffrey
and Andrea in Hazel.

390
00:22:58,833 --> 00:23:01,767
And besides, it looks like
things turned out okay.

391
00:23:01,900 --> 00:23:02,867
She calmed down

392
00:23:03,000 --> 00:23:04,467
and looks like she won't cause
any more trouble.

393
00:23:04,600 --> 00:23:06,033
She calmed down?

394
00:23:06,167 --> 00:23:07,767
Don't be too sure.

395
00:23:14,533 --> 00:23:17,300
Seems like Paz still
of being nice, friend.

396
00:23:19,133 --> 00:23:21,767
I don't care
about that Amazon girl.

397
00:23:21,900 --> 00:23:25,633
What matters to me
is convincing Manuel,

398
00:23:25,800 --> 00:23:28,600
Jessica, and, of course, Felma.

399
00:23:35,233 --> 00:23:38,100
You're such a great actress,
Friend.

400
00:23:38,233 --> 00:23:40,567
I can't even imagine how many
gallons of fake tears

401
00:23:40,700 --> 00:23:42,633
you cried in front of them.

402
00:23:43,667 --> 00:23:45,500
Well, actually...

403
00:23:45,633 --> 00:23:48,633
I only pretended in front
of Manuel and Felma.

404
00:23:49,667 --> 00:23:53,067
But every word I said
to Jessica was true.

405
00:23:53,967 --> 00:23:55,000
And from my heart.

406
00:23:56,067 --> 00:23:57,900
Let's see,
let's check it first.

407
00:23:58,033 --> 00:23:59,300
Oh, no, this is broken, Ian.

408
00:23:59,433 --> 00:24:01,867
Oh, no, bring this inside
and replace the box.

409
00:24:02,000 --> 00:24:03,533
Then check
the items inside, okay?

410
00:24:03,667 --> 00:24:05,400
- Yes, Ma'am.
- Okay.

411
00:24:05,533 --> 00:24:07,900
I'm reminding you, Friend.

412
00:24:08,033 --> 00:24:10,467
Watch out for Hazel.

413
00:24:10,600 --> 00:24:13,433
Don't trust that little squeak.

414
00:24:13,567 --> 00:24:14,733
She's smart.

415
00:24:14,867 --> 00:24:17,267
Who knows? She's got some bad
thoughts brewing.

416
00:24:19,933 --> 00:24:22,333
She said yes to Jessica's terms.

417
00:24:22,467 --> 00:24:24,000
If she tries
to mess with them again,

418
00:24:24,133 --> 00:24:27,100
she could lose her child.

419
00:24:27,233 --> 00:24:28,933
So, if that happens?

420
00:24:29,100 --> 00:24:30,633
What's next?

421
00:24:30,767 --> 00:24:33,300
You'll be Jessica's mother?

422
00:24:33,433 --> 00:24:34,533
Sis!

423
00:24:34,667 --> 00:24:36,967
Someone might hear you.

424
00:24:37,100 --> 00:24:38,333
Just saying, Friend.

425
00:24:38,467 --> 00:24:40,467
Just a friendly reminder.

426
00:24:40,600 --> 00:24:44,800
You have children
who needs your attention more.

427
00:24:48,133 --> 00:24:49,367
If only you knew.

428
00:24:50,300 --> 00:24:53,033
I text my kids every single day

429
00:24:53,167 --> 00:24:55,233
to Jeffrey and Andrea.

430
00:24:56,500 --> 00:24:57,733
But until now...

431
00:24:59,133 --> 00:25:00,867
none of them has replied yet.

432
00:25:01,000 --> 00:25:03,733
But how long will you pretend
to be nice?

433
00:25:04,867 --> 00:25:06,167
For Manuel and Jessica,

434
00:25:07,567 --> 00:25:09,300
as long as it takes.

435
00:25:09,433 --> 00:25:11,533
Until I win back their trust.

436
00:25:12,800 --> 00:25:14,467
But to that Flirty Felma,

437
00:25:15,500 --> 00:25:17,500
I'll keep the act
until I ruin her.

438
00:25:19,200 --> 00:25:20,800
Oh, well.

439
00:25:20,933 --> 00:25:23,867
I'm taking a break
from bothering my family.

440
00:25:24,000 --> 00:25:26,767
Let's focus on her, there.

441
00:25:26,900 --> 00:25:29,100
That longanisa vendor.

442
00:25:37,033 --> 00:25:38,267
Daisy.

443
00:25:38,400 --> 00:25:40,100
He got me into Shop Point
Express.

444
00:25:40,233 --> 00:25:41,100
I'll work as a rider.

445
00:25:41,233 --> 00:25:42,267
Do you know how to ride
a motorcycle?

446
00:25:42,400 --> 00:25:43,700
Thank you for coming.

447
00:25:43,833 --> 00:25:45,267
Thank you, Ma'am Andrea.

448
00:25:45,400 --> 00:25:46,600
I'm excited to earn.

449
00:25:46,733 --> 00:25:47,900
It's a sure bet, isn't it?

450
00:25:48,033 --> 00:25:50,133
I put all my savings into this
because I believe in you.

451
00:25:50,267 --> 00:25:51,533
What's your plan with all these?

452
00:25:51,667 --> 00:25:53,800
I want to take down FMP,
remember?

453
00:25:53,933 --> 00:25:56,233
- We'll start from here.
- Poison?

454
00:25:56,367 --> 00:25:58,033
She's the one who served
hotdogs and sisig

455
00:25:58,167 --> 00:25:59,767
- at the feeding earlier.
- What's going on?

456
00:25:59,900 --> 00:26:02,600
Everyone who ate the sisig
she served

457
00:26:02,733 --> 00:26:03,767
got food poisoning!

458
00:26:03,900 --> 00:26:07,167
"<i> Sisig ni Bunso</i> "
is of high quality, made by FMP.

459
00:26:07,300 --> 00:26:08,633
You're all scoundrels!

460
00:26:08,800 --> 00:26:11,667
- No, don't ever...
- What's going on? Paz.

461
00:26:11,800 --> 00:26:12,767
Take care of these.

462
00:26:12,900 --> 00:26:14,033
High value 'yan.
